{#-
  Menubar — Horizontal app-style nav bar of N DropdownMenu submenus
  (File / Edit / View / Help). Pure orchestrator wrap; each child is a
  fully standalone DropdownMenu.

  Per OQ-30 (sealed S2.3a opening): per-submenu DropdownMenus + thin
  menubar orchestrator (~70 effective controller lines). Per WAI-ARIA APG
  "Menubar (menu of menus)". Per S2.3b doctrine: keyboard-first; hover-open
  is opt-in for a future Phase 4 amend if demand emerges.

  Composes:
    - menubar Stimulus controller (orchestrator).
    - N child DropdownMenu compounds (consumer-provided via {% block menus %}).

  Parameters:
    htmlId     (string,  optional) — auto-generated.
    label      (string,  optional) — aria-label on the menubar wrap (e.g.
                                      'Application' or 'Main navigation').
                                      Use when no visible heading nearby.
    labelledBy (string,  optional) — aria-labelledby reference to a heading
                                      id. Preferred over label when a
                                      visible heading exists.
    className  (string,  optional) — extra classes on the wrap.

  Blocks:
    menus (required) — N DropdownMenu embeds (or compatible Popover-based
                       compounds). Each child's trigger MUST stamp
                       `data-menubar-target="trigger"` (so Menubar can find
                       it for the roving nav) AND `data-popover-target="trigger"`
                       (so its co-mounted Popover wires the anchor).
                       Strongly recommend the `.theme-menubar__trigger`
                       class for the standard visual.

  Usage example (3 submenus):

    {% embed '@theme/components/menubar/menubar.html.twig' with {
      label: 'Menubar principal'|trans,
    } %}
      {% block menus %}
        {% embed '@theme/components/dropdown-menu/dropdown-menu.html.twig' %}
          {% block trigger %}
            <button type="button" class="theme-menubar__trigger"
                    data-popover-target="trigger"
                    data-menubar-target="trigger"
                    aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false">
              {{ 'Fichier'|trans }}
            </button>
          {% endblock %}
          {% block items %}
            {% include '@theme/components/item/item.html.twig' with {
              label: 'Nouveau'|trans, iconLeading: 'plus', kbdShortcut: ['⌘', 'N'], as: 'div',
            } %}
            ...
          {% endblock %}
        {% endembed %}
        {# ... more submenus ... #}
      {% endblock %}
    {% endembed %}
-#}

{%- set htmlId     = htmlId     | default('theme-menubar-' ~ random()) -%}
{%- set label      = label      | default(null) -%}
{%- set labelledBy = labelledBy | default(null) -%}
{%- set className  = className  | default('') -%}

{%- set _classes = ['theme-menubar'] -%}
{%- if className -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge([className]) -%}{%- endif -%}

<div
  id="{{ htmlId }}"
  class="{{ _classes | join(' ') }}"
  data-controller="menubar"
  data-action="keydown->menubar#keydown"
  {%- if label %} aria-label="{{ label }}"{% endif -%}
  {%- if labelledBy %} aria-labelledby="{{ labelledBy }}"{% endif -%}
>
  {%- block menus -%}{%- endblock -%}
</div>
